Class ResourceTypeToValue

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.google.common.collect.ForwardingObject
      • com.google.common.collect.ForwardingMap<String,com.google.common.primitives.UnsignedInteger>
        • org.jclouds.ultradns.ws.ResourceTypeToValue
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.google.common.base.Function<Object,String>, com.google.common.collect.BiMap<String,com.google.common.primitives.UnsignedInteger>, Map<String,com.google.common.primitives.UnsignedInteger>

    @Beta
public class ResourceTypeToValue
extends com.google.common.collect.ForwardingMap<String,com.google.common.primitives.UnsignedInteger>
implements com.google.common.base.Function<Object,String>, com.google.common.collect.BiMap<String,com.google.common.primitives.UnsignedInteger>
    Most UltraDNS commands use the numerical type value of a resource record rather than their names. This class helps convert the numerical values to what people more commonly use. Note that this does not complain a complete mapping and may need updates over time.
    Author:
    Adrian Cole
    See Also:
    ParamParser
